            . I am in the employ of James Harris, <rs id="t18280529-262-viclabel1441" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-262-victim1408 t18280529-262-viclabel1441"></join>, of <placeName id="t18280529-262-crimeloc1442">Fore-street, City</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-262-crimeloc1442" type="placeName" value="Fore-street, City"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-262-crimeloc1442" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-262-off1439 t18280529-262-crimeloc1442"></join>. On the 28th of May, at half-past eight o'clock in the evening, the prisoner and a boy came into the shop together; I saw the boy draw his hand from a drawer of ribbons on the counter, and give something to the prisoner - I taxed them with it, and before I could get round the counter they ran off, and the prisoner dropped these ribbons against the door: they are my master's property; I followed, and never lost sight of him till the officer took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-262-person1410">
